UNITED STATES of America, Appellant, v. Jose DOMINGUEZ, Appellee. No. 6201. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. July 28, 1930.

Before WILBUR), Circuit Judge, anld LOUDERBACK, District Judge.

PER CURIAM.

Upon motion of counsel for the appellant, ordered appeal dismissed, that a decree of dismissal be filed and entered accordingly, and that the mandate of this court issue forthwith.
